:5,"text":"Hmm, I remember that in barium enemas, the transition zone is where the contrast changes from the right to the left, and the ratio is usually 6:1 (recto-sigmoid ratio).","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038238,0.064303,0.079729,0.094106,0.10331,0.10828,0.10974,0.1036,0.094052,0.083155,0.067257,0.054237],"unified_progress":[0.033001,0.061759,0.081477,0.09641,0.10195,0.11434,0.10488,0.098496,0.094542,0.087276,0.069654,0.056217]},{"section":6,"text":"If the ratio is reversed, that might indicate something wrong with the function of the sigmoid colon.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042985,0.05634,0.073762,0.08761,0.09657,0.1019,0.10579,0.10313,0.097787,0.090538,0.077377,0.06621],"unified_progress":[0.038358,0.059711,0.07737,0.090525,0.097248,0.10395,0.10321,0.10065,0.097475,0.091332,0.077424,0.062744]},{"section":7,"text":"I think this is a sign of Hirschsprung's disease.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029347,0.05555,0.073799,0.088146,0.093329,0.097198,0.10386,0.10144,0.097722,0.10156,0.083777,0.074271],"unified_progress":[0.028461,0.058814,0.077791,0.091441,0.09613,0.099789,0.10326,0.10213,0.099551,0.095664,0.081773,0.065189]},{"section":8,"text":"Hirschsprung's affects the lower part of the colon and causes it to be in a state of constant contraction, so the barium can't move past it easily.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.020943,0.040644,0.059288,0.073891,0.09387,0.10649,0.11278,0.11932,0.1182,0.10091,0.082631,0.071035],"unified_progress":[0.024088,0.05022,0.073199,0.088617,0.098396,0.11253,0.1116,0.10887,0.10358,0.095837,0.076366,0.056688]},{"section":9,"text":"The patient's symptoms of constipation and abdominal distension also fit with Hirschsprung's because the bowel can't push everything through, leading to constipation.","dimension":9,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03954,0.06075,0.066326,0.07