's consider other possibilities too.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.10578,0.084929,0.079063,0.07089,0.072462,0.075718,0.079914,0.091126,0.084867,0.060116,0.065922,0.12922],"unified_progress":[0.19418,0.074858,0.0614,0.062667,0.071952,0.073598,0.095509,0.084458,0.083247,0.069603,0.065104,0.063423]},{"section":13,"text":"Could it be something like intussusception?","dimension":4,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027645,0.050922,0.069966,0.085783,0.093449,0.1013,0.10976,0.11311,0.11426,0.11135,0.080192,0.042262],"unified_progress":[0.036305,0.067267,0.065377,0.093805,0.1035,0.10091,0.10155,0.10649,0.1019,0.094042,0.077357,0.051494]},{"section":14,"text":"But that's more common in younger kids and usually comes with sudden symptoms, not a slow build-up over two years.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043448,0.048447,0.056464,0.065404,0.075556,0.087533,0.099778,0.10967,0.11858,0.12298,0.10588,0.06626],"unified_progress":[0.046479,0.061656,0.072636,0.080074,0.089861,0.096286,0.097188,0.10192,0.10024,0.10024,0.087149,0.066273]},{"section":15,"text":"Plus, intussusception would show different imaging findings.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.020267,0.033453,0.047793,0.061195,0.074646,0.090692,0.10708,0.12309,0.13565,0.1393,0.10961,0.05722],"unified_progress":[0.031534,0.053523,0.069991,0.07977,0.091042,0.096638,0.10058,0.10542,0.1059,0.1092,0.092124,0.064274]},{"section":16,"text":"What about malrotation?","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.010578,0.028014,0.044583,0.059487,0.074446,0.093771,0.11328,0.13445,0.14819,0.14864,0.10404,0.040515],"unified_progress":[0.02378,0.051915,0.069303,0.080389,0.09162,0.096558,0.10308,0.10938,0.10921,0.11608,0.092374,0.056314]},{"section":17,"text":"Well, that can cause midgut volvulus, but again, it typically presents acutely, not chronically like this.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_dege