id is wider than the rectum, right?","dimension":6,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036,0.076853,0.088906,0.097218,0.10075,0.10148,0.10124,0.094961,0.093051,0.08056,0.071623,0.057361],"unified_progress":[0.094967,0.076619,0.086945,0.095007,0.099611,0.099237,0.094863,0.089989,0.084157,0.072455,0.058825,0.047326]},{"section":11,"text":"If that's reversed, maybe the rectum is narrower than the sigmoid.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040167,0.081941,0.091827,0.097927,0.098195,0.098666,0.097295,0.091484,0.092203,0.080177,0.069867,0.060252],"unified_progress":[0.062455,0.080287,0.096282,0.10292,0.10587,0.10053,0.096451,0.09019,0.085567,0.071721,0.058499,0.049221]},{"section":12,"text":"Wait, Hirschsprung's disease comes to mind.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039611,0.076308,0.091667,0.098332,0.099513,0.095555,0.094344,0.089733,0.084952,0.086562,0.072867,0.070556],"unified_progress":[0.05073,0.069641,0.085333,0.096571,0.096964,0.10185,0.097183,0.092554,0.087253,0.086275,0.072845,0.0628]},{"section":13,"text":"That's a congenital condition where there's aganglionic bowel segment, leading to obstruction.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032905,0.069777,0.084865,0.097663,0.10477,0.10532,0.10407,0.095438,0.086599,0.086755,0.069325,0.062506],"unified_progress":[0.037423,0.061644,0.083894,0.095562,0.10118,0.11031,0.10455,0.10042,0.093962,0.086821,0.069223,0.055018]},{"section":14,"text":"The transition zone is a classic finding in Hirschsprung's, where the normal ganglionic cells abruptly end, causing a narrowing.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034516,0.07345,0.08603,0.09613,0.10095,0.10253,0.10186,0.094109,0.08954,0.08651,0.069853,0.064522],"unified_progress":[0.036956,0.064568,0.084471,0.097484,0.10236,0.1072,0.10318,0.098933,0.094791,0.0839,0.06902,0.057141]},{"section":15,"text":"The barium would show the transition